channel.name: HSDS_FHIR_Listener_Facade
channel.description:
NOTE: This channel depends on the following variables being declared in the configuration map for "search" into FHIR persistent:
fhirDBDatabaseType: The type of database server (postgres, sqlserver). fhirDBDriver: The JDBC Driver class to use when connecting to the FHIR database. fhirDBUrl: The JDBC connection URL to use when connecting to the FHIR database. fhirDBUsername: The username to use when connecting to the FHIR database. fhirDBPassword: The password to use when connecting to the FHIR database. fhirDBMaxRetries: The maximum amount of retry attempts when a database connection fails.
NOTE: This channel depends on the following variables being declared in the Deploy script of the channel for "search_facade" for HSDS:
hsdsDBDatabaseType: The type of database server (postgres, sqlserver). hsdsDBDriver: The JDBC Driver class to use when connecting to the FHIR database. hsdsDBUrl: The JDBC connection URL to use when connecting to the FHIR database. hsdsDBUsername: The username to use when connecting to the FHIR database. hsdsDBPassword: The password to use when connecting to the FHIR database.

codeTemplateLibrary.name: caseXML Library
codeTemplateLibrary.description:
This library was added upon migration to version 3.3.0. It includes all pre-existing code templates, and is set to be included on all pre-existing and new channels.
You should create your own new libraries and assign code templates to them as you see fit. You should also link libraries to specific channels, so that you're not necessarily including all code templates on all channels all the time.
